TASK_DESCRIPTION=Task Reviewer (pane 1.1) is stuck in a tight spin loop: calls 'doey msg count --to 1.1' → 0 messages → runs reviewer-wait.sh → returns WAKE_REASON=ACTIVE_TASKS → loops immediately again. This burns context for nothing. Commit bfe7673 claimed to add a passive-role fast path to taskmaster-wait.sh to prevent this for reviewer/deployment/expert — but the reviewer is still doing it. Either: (1) reviewer-wait.sh itself is missing the passive fast path, (2) ACTIVE_TASKS wake reason is firing when there's no work actually assigned to the reviewer, (3) the wake hook isn't sleeping/blocking long enough. Fix: reviewer should only wake when a task is explicitly assigned to it for review, not on any ACTIVE_TASKS signal. Investigate .claude/hooks/reviewer-wait.sh and taskmaster-wait.sh passive fast path.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W4.1: investigate reviewer-wait path + fix passive-role fast path to prevent spin loop:done
